title: Johnston Murray
added: Through these activities Johnston Murray had increased his own name recognition, and was also known as the son of the well-known politician and ninth governor of the state, William H. Murray. Johnston Murray was elected Governor of Oklahoma in [[1950 Oklahoma gubernatorial election|November 1950]] and sworn into office on January 21, 1951. His 81-year old father, "Alfalfa Bill" Murray, administered the oath of office.
